fedsynthct_lietal_t1w_brain.description:
This model was trained using FedSynthCT-Brain, a federated learning framework for brain MRI-to-CT translation.
Input: T1-weighted MRI scans.
Preprocess: N4ITK Bias Field Correction, Crop/Pad/Resize.
Output: Synthetic CT volume [256x256x256].
How to cite:
If you use this model, please cite:
C.B. Raggio et al, FedSynthCT-Brain: A federated learning framework for multi-institutional brain MRI-to-CT synthesis, Computers in Biology and Medicine, Volume 192, Part A, 2025, 110160, ISSN 0010-4825, https://doi.org/10.1016/j.compbiomed.2025.110160.

unet2pix_t1_t2.description:
Generates a synthetic T2-weighted MRI slice ONLY for the central axial slice of the input volume.
Input: Brain MRI T1w
Output: Input volume with the central slice replaced by the synthetic T2w.
Note: Input is resized to 224x192 for inference and scaled back.
Citation:
Moschetto et al., Medical I2I Benchmark.
